U.S.: Repeating is the mother of wisdom
It is funny that Barack Obama, the president with the reputation of the smartest man, as a diligent student repeats in the Afghan question the strategy of his predecessor, whom he himself took for the stupidest.
When he finally revealed his Afghan approach, eagerly awaited, it was demonstrated that it was a copy of the script used for Iraq by Bush, created three years ago.
Not only in the same text is the phrase "same as in Iraq" used several times, but it also did not hesitate to use the title of the January 2007 Bush Declaration for its own statement: "A new way forward".
It was himself, who three years ago criticised Bush's idea of sending new military reinforcements to Iraq, the country that is suffering from civil war, and that criticized him as "an irresponsible decision with catastrophic consequences."
The following months, however, showed that Bush's strategy, based on the recommendations of the field captains, was the only possible and successful, so that today nothing about Iraq is spoken of in the news.
Bush's reputation did not improve, but objectively left his successor a much more favourable initial situation than he could have expected.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama expects the miracle to be repeated.
The field captains again asked him to increase the military contingent, especially the chief of the Afghan General Stanley McCristal operation. He, even in spite of the traditional subordinated relations, subjected the indecisive rifles in the White House to a harsh criticism.
He asked 40,000 men to improve the situation.
The president hesitated for three months, but nothing better happened to him, so at least he tricked the general about 10,000 soldiers.
He managed to get Europe to promise him another 5,000, although he had previously had at least 10,000.
The most problematic of Obama's entire strategy seems to be his goal, to start withdrawing the troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and ending this procedure in three years. Obama's whole doctrine generated more questions from the answers he was offering.
Many doubt that the increase is the same as the procedure in Iraq.
Despite the fratriculated wars in recent years, Iraq's society is relatively well organized, its leaders respect the agreements.
The situation in Afghanistan is different: it is not possible to trust anyone and no agreement is reached.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare the Afghan security forces, if they are used to changing the boss daily according to their needs.
Political institutions, although formally established, will remain only a people of Potemkin. After him the tribal patriarchal relations will remain.
Balancing the interests of different ethnic groups is extremely complicated due to confusing relations, even more complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Not even establishing a state that is "action capable", a minimum objective of the entire operation, seems very real.
The horizon of Obama's strategy is shocked by its volunteerism.
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has continued to deteriorate and is now about to collapse.
Only a romantic soul, who knows nothing about reality, can believe that the military sent to the war to "come home soon", will do some miracle here.
From a political point of view, setting the date of withdrawal of troops is purely irresponsibility, as the Taliban will consider it an indirect statement of the U.S. defeat.
The last NATO summit showed that Europeans are increasingly less willing to participate in military operations in Afghanistan.
European politicians do not know, nor do they want to explain to their voters, what the security of Germany or Italy has to do with the war with Hindu Kush.
The other factor, capable of radically affecting the situation, is the development of events in Iran.
If the situation continues to deteriorate and increased sanctions have no effect on Iranians, the US will have to make a difficult decision: try to solve the problem with military force or not.
It will be necessary to seek the answers precisely when, according to Obama, America begins the triumphal withdrawal of the Afghan troops.
However, each solution will mean a dramatic reversal for the Afghan situation.
The only positive point for Barack Obama is the lack of three years for presidential elections, and that is why there is still a lot of time left to find another strategy, if this is a total failure.
